Task 2: Student Digital Portfolio

GitHub is a platform where developers store and manage their code using Git, which keeps track of changes made over time. 
I created a profile README that works like a short introduction. I added my basic details such as my branch, year, and 
what I want to learn. Even though it’s simple, it’s important because it’s the first thing people notice on a GitHub profile.

LinkedIn is a professional networking platform used by companies and recruiters, so creating a profile felt necessary. 
I added my education details, including VIT Bhopal, my course, and expected graduation year. I don’t have much experience 
to add yet, but at least my profile is set up properly.

Kaggle is a platform by Google that focuses on data science and machine learning. I signed up because of my AI/ML course. 
I haven’t explored it much yet, but it will be useful later.

Overall, setting up these profiles made me realize that building a professional presence should start early. I plan to keep 
updating them as I gain more skills and experience.
